HEADWORD: Conformability
<hw>Con*form`a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The state of being conformable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The parallelism of two sets of
strata which are in contact.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Conformable</ent>⟦br⟧
